<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Skewer_Sim_Control" s="74221">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0xD1C36CD8<!--String: "Skewer & Sim Control"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skewer_and_Sim_Control_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6895974465ce7a7a</T>
      <T n="text">0x97A75EBE<!--String: "The Sim thumbnails that appear at the bottom left of the screen, which include your household members, is called the Skewer.\n\nThe Skewer provides quick access to information about all the Sims in your Household, as well as the ability to issue commands to them."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skewer_and_Sim_Control_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6895974465ce7a79</T>
      <T n="text">0x5B841426<!--String: "Left click on a Sim in the Skewer to select them.  You can also use the [spacebar] to switch between the Sims in your household.\n\nRight click on the thumbnail of a Sim to set the camera to Follow Mode (an icon will indicate who you are following). Now when your Sim moves, you will follow them. Just move your camera to unset Follow Mode."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skewer_and_Sim_Control_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6895974465ce7a78</T>
      <T n="text">0x7A002787<!--String: "The color background of a Sims thumbnail will indicate their current Emotion."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skewer_and_Sim_Control_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6895974465ce7a7f</T>
      <T n="text">0x5F21245F<!--String: "The Home icon will appear when your Sim is away from their home lot. Clicking this will send them home."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Skewer_and_Sim_Control_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:6895974465ce7a7e</T>
      <T n="text">0x9C20224F<!--String: "An Away Action icon appears for Sims who are not currently on the same Street. Clicking it will open different options for you to direct your Sims from afar (socialize, care for self, or other).  The available options depend on where they are (at work, visiting friends, etc...).\n\nYou can also choose to bring that Sim to you, or send yourself to that Sim through this menu."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">195</T>
</I>